                                <li>Listen to your specific complaints and goals</li>
                                <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy/li>
                                <li>Discuss recommendations regarding surgical or nonsurgical techniques that may help you achieve your goals</li>
                                <li>surgical procedures that are offered and which approach is right for you</li>
                                <li>Preoperative photographs will be taken and the surgical plan will be analyzed for you with use of your photographs</li>
                                <li>The risks and benefits of surgery will be thoroughly outlined for you</li>
                                <li>You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from both our physicians and staff regarding inverted nipple repair and any other surgical or nonsurgical procedures you may be interested in</li>
                                <li>You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding the procedure including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after inverted nipple repair</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="text-section text-bg-grey mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6 " id="section-day-of-expect">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can I expect the day of my Inverted Nipple Repair in Houston, Texas?</h3>
                                <p>If inverted nipple repair is to be performed alone, it will likely be performed in the procedure room at The Oaks Plastic Surgery Clinic. When you arrive at The Oaks Plastic Surgery Clinic, you will be brought back to the procedure room. You will be given medication to make you comfortable and numbing cream will be placed to eliminate or minimize the pain of local anesthetic injections. Once you are completely numb, Dr. Danielle Andry or Dr. Nandi Wijay will perform the procedure. The procedure typically takes between 30 minutes and one hour to perform. Afterwards, you will have a very bulky dressing, which helps keep the nipples in the correct position and protects the repair. This dressing will be removed 5 - 7 days post operatively.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="call-shedule">
